French Ligue 1 side OGC Nice have now jumped to the front queue in the chase for Terem Moffi after they put in an improved offer of €20 Million for the Super Eagles striker. Ouest-France has reported that Nice, who are known as The Eagles (Les Aiglons) have now offered a deal estimated at €20m with €17m paid upfront and €3m worth of bonuses. to his club (FC Lorient) to accept or again reject.” Ineos-owned Nice have already offered €15m and €18m, but both offers were rejected by Lorient. A physical, fast and powerful forward, Moffi scored 35 goals in 90 games since his arrival in Brittany two years ago for an €8m fee. His contract expires in 2024.